-- Lindsey Vonn Captures First Women's Downhill Title of Season in France
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-12-18T15:09:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-18/lindsey-vonn-captures-first-women-s-downhill-title-of-season-in-france.html
Lindsey Vonn of the U.S. won her
first downhill race of the season today in Val d’Isere, France.  Vonn, the three-time defending World Cup champion, finished
in a time of 1 minute, 51.42 seconds to beat out Switzerland’s
Lara Gut by 0.66 seconds. The 26-year-old American had finished
second to Germany’s Maria Riesch in the season’s first two
downhills.  The victory moves Vonn to the top of the downhill standings
ahead of Riesch, who leads Vonn by 52 points in the overall
table. Riesch finished 24th today, 2.28 seconds behind Vonn.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  